0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 198 "8.   Numerical Appr
oximations.  While Maple can perform exact arithmetic, there are times
 when it is important or helpful to obtain a decimal approximation for
 some exact answer.  For instance, the " }{TEXT 275 5 "solve" }{TEXT 
-1 66 " command can be used to find the \"exact\" roots of the polynom
ial  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "p := x^3-11*x^2-70*x+600;" "6#>%\"pG,**$%\"xG\"
\"$\"\"\"*&\"#6F)*$F'\"\"#F)!\"\"*&\"#qF)F'F)F.\"$+'F)" }{TEXT -1 34 "
 .  Execute the following command:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 43 "roots_of_p := solve(x^3-11*x
^2-70*x+600,x);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 289 "That isn't very illuminating.  It maybe hard to tell, bu
t there are three roots.  If you change the problem slightly, it may b
e even harder.  (For example, change the number 70 in the above proble
m to 80 and then do the calculation!)  To display each root separately
, execute the commands:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r1 := Re(roots_of_p[1]);" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r2 := Re(roots_of_p[2]);" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 24 "r3 := Re(roots_of_p[3]);" }
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 47 "Even th
at isn't all that helpful.  The command " }{TEXT 276 5 "evalf" }{TEXT 
